e" stretchy=3D"false">}</mo></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container>, wh=
ich translates to =E2=80=9Call real numbers <em>x </em>such that <em>x </em=
>is greater than or equal to 4.=E2=80=9D Notice that braces are used to ind=
icate a set.</p>
<p>The third method is <strong>interval notation</strong>, in which solutio=
n sets are indicated with parentheses or brackets. The solutions to <mjx-co=
ntainer class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" =
ctxtmenu_counter=3D"3" style=3D"font-size: 109.4%; position: relative;"><mj=
x-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-=
c class=3D"mjx-c1D465 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mo class=3D"mjx-n" space=
=3D"4"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c2265"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mn class=3D"mjx-n" =
